SUMMARY:Arbor Day Tree Giveaway
DTSTART:20260427T100000
DTEND:20260427T130000
UID:f8352be28de499aa1b73c4ef1f7ca871@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:For more than a decade\, Sycamore Land Trust’s annual “Arb
 or Day Tree Giveaway” has distributed hundreds of free tree seedlings ea
 ch Arbor Day to help our community create beneficial native habitat at hom
 e. Planting trees creates food and shelter for wildlife\, absorbs carbon d
 ioxide\, and stores carbon in the soil. This year\, Sycamore will distribu
 te over 600 tree seedlings at Bloomingfoods East &amp\; Near West. For mor
 e information about tree species and planting information\, visit sycamore
 landtrust.org/free-trees.
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2024/03/arbor-day-tree-giveaway-3/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Earth Day Preserve-a-Preserve Weed Wrangle
DTSTART:20260422T100000
DTEND:20260422T120000
UID:a293c19d42c9d5de665818b5523bd666@sycamorelandtrust.org
DESCRIPTION:Volunteers are invited to join Sycamore in celebration of Eart
 h Day by helping maintain habitat at our preserves! Weed Wrangle events ar
 e fun and educational opportunities to learn how to identify and control t
 he invasive plants that are negatively impacting our natural areas and oth
 er green spaces. The focus for this work day will be the identification an
 d control of garlic mustard at Laura Hare Nature Preserve\, in Brown Count
 y.
LOCATION:The Laura Hare Nature Preserve at Downey Hill
URL:https://sycamorelandtrust.org/2024/02/earth-day-preserve-a-preserve-we
 ed-wrangle/
X-SOURCE:Sycamore Land Trust
